## OUTPUT FORMAT
{{.OutputFormatSnippet}}
{{if .OutputSchemaSnippet}}
- `verification.id` is the same UUID as the input `finding.id`; copy that actual UUID, never the `<uuid-v4>` placeholder
- `verification.verdict` is one of `confirmed`, `refuted`, `unverified`
- `verification.priority` is an integer 0-3
- `verification.confidence_score` is a number between 0 and 1 expressing your confidence in the verdict
- `verification.remarks` is a short markdown explanation of the verdict; when `refuted`, MUST cite the concrete code or invariant that contradicts the finding
  - add paragraphs, e.g. an empty line, between distinct points to improve readability
  - put code references and symbol names in backticks or code blocks
  - format bold or italic when it makes sense to emphasize a point
{{end}}
